2026-06-17 16:07:11 | DEBUG    | openai._base_client  | Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/deployments/text-embedding-3-small/embeddings', 'headers': {'api-key': '<redacted>'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-99a91ef3-50c3-441b-a449-d71b225887c2', 'post_parser': <function Embeddings.create.<locals>.parser at 0x0000020C36E16350>, 'security': {'bearer_auth': True}, 'content': None, 'json_data': {'input': ['7 4.', 'If Rs is the equivalent resistance of the given series combination of resistances, figure, then the potential difference across A and B is, V = IRs.', 'We have IRs = I (R1 + R2 + R3) or s 1 2 3 R R R R \x01 \x02 \x02 Memory note In a series resistance circuit, it should be noted that : (i) the current is same in every resistor.', '(ii) the current in the circuit is independent of the relative positions of the various resistors in the series.', '(iii) the voltage across any resistor is directly proportional to the resistance of the resistor.', '(iv) the total resistance of the circuit is equal to the sum of the individual resistances, plus the internal resistance of a cell if any.', '(v) The total resistance in the series circuit is obviously more than the greatest resistance in the circuit.', '8.2  Resistances in Parallel Any number of resistors are said to be connected in parallel if potential difference across each of them is the same and is equal to the applied potential difference.', '1.', 'Let V be the potential difference applied across A and B with the help of a battery \x1f.', '2.', 'Let I be the main current in the circuit from battery.', 'I divides itself into three unequal parts because the resistances of these branches are different and I1, I2, I3 be the current through the resistances R1, R2 and R3 respectively.', 'Then, I = I2 + I2 + I3 3.', 'Here, potential difference across each resistor is V, therefore V = I1R1 = I2 R2 = I3R3 or 1 2 3 1 2 3 V V V I , I , I R R R \x01 \x01 \x01 Putting values, we get 1 2 3 V V V I R R R \x01 \x02 \x02 4.', 'If Rp is the equivalent resistance of the given parallel combination of resistance, figure, then V = IRp or I = V/Rp we have p 1 2 3 V V V V R R R R \x01 \x02 \x02 or p 1 2 3 1 1 1 1 R R R R \x01 \x02 \x02 Thus, the reciprocal of equivalent resistance of a number of resistor connected in parallel is equal to the sum of the reciprocals of the individual resistances.', 'Memory note In a parallel resistance circuit, it should be noted that : (i) the potential difference across each resistor is the same and is equal to the applied potential difference.', '(ii) the current through each resistor is inversely proportional to the resistance of that resistor.', '(iii) total current through the parallel combination is the sum of the individual currents through the various resistors.', '(iv) The reciprocal of the total resistance of the parallel combination is equal to the sum of the reciprocals of the individual resistances.', '(v) The total resistances are connected in series, the current through each resistance is same.', 'When the resistance are in parallel, the pot-diff.', 'accross each resistance is the same and not the current.', 'JEE | NEET | Class 8 - 10 Download eSaral App www.esaral.com Rev.', 'Notes Class 12 Physics Chapter-2'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
