d will be maximum when r R \x01  so 2 max E P 4r \x01 .', 'This statement in generalised from is called “maximum power transfer theorem”.', '(vii) When the cell is being charged i.e.', 'current is given to the cell then E = V – ir  and E < V.', '(2) Open circuit : When no current is taken from the cell  it is said to be in open circuit.', '(i) Current through the circuit i = 0 (ii) Potential difference between A and B, VAB = E (iii) Potential difference between C and D, VCD = 0 (3) Short circuit : If two terminals of cell are join together by a thick conducting wire JEE | NEET | Class 8 - 10 Download eSaral App www.esaral.com Rev.', 'Notes Class 12 Physics Chapter-2'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
