raphs (i) Slope of Q vs t graph gives instantaneous current.', '(ii) Area under the I vs t graph gives net charge flown.', '11.', 'KIRCHHOFF’S LAW 11.1  Kirchhoff’s first law or Kirchhoff’s junction law or Kirchhoff’s current law.', '1.', 'the algebraic sum of the currents meeting at a junction in a closed electric circuit is zero, i.e., I 0 % \x01 2.', 'Consider a junction O in the electrical circuit at which the five conductors are meeting.', 'Let I1, I2, I3, I4 and I5 be the currents in these conductors in directions, shown in figure, JEE | NEET | Class 8 - 10 Download eSaral App www.esaral.com Rev.', 'Notes Class 12 Physics Chapter-2'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
