2026-06-17 16:07:23 | DEBUG    | openai._base_client  | Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/deployments/text-embedding-3-small/embeddings', 'headers': {'api-key': '<redacted>'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-c007281e-a8a0-4b46-abdd-7933a674a37c', 'post_parser': <function Embeddings.create.<locals>.parser at 0x0000020C3C1209E0>, 'security': {'bearer_auth': True}, 'content': None, 'json_data': {'input': ['19 If applied voltage is constant then (consumed) 1 P R \x01 (By 2 A V P R \x02 ).', 'Hence if different bulbs (electrical appliance) operated at same voltage supply then consumed R 1 P P thickness R \x01 \x01 \x01 Different bulbs \x03 Resistance R25 > R100 > R1000 \x03 Thickness of filament t1000– > t100 > t40 \x03 Brightness B1000 > B100 > B25 (6) Long distance power transmission : When power is transmitted through a power line of resistance R, power- loss will be R i2 Now if the power P is transmitted at voltage V P = Vi  i.e.', 'i = (P/V)  So, 2 2 P Power loss R V \x02 \x04 Now as for a given power and line, P and R are constant so Power loss \x01 (1/V2) So if power is transmitted at high voltage, power loss will be small and vice-versa.', 'e.g., power loss at 22 kV is 10–4 times than at 220 V.', 'This is why long distance power transmission is carried out at high voltage.', '(7) Time taken by heater to boil the water : We know that heat required to raise the temperature \x05\x06 of any substance of mass m and specific heat S is H = m.S.\x05\x06 Here heat produced by the heater = Heat required to raise the temp.', '\x05\x06 of water.', 'i.e.', 'p \x04 t = J \x04 m.S.\x05\x06 \x03\x07 J(m.S.', ') t p \x05\x06 \x02 {J = 4.18 or 4.2 J/cal) for m kg water 4180(or 4200)m t p \x05\x06 \x02 {S = 1000 cal/kgoC) If quantity of water is given n litre then 4180(4200)n t p \x05\x06 \x02 13.2  Electric Energy The total electric work done or energy supplied by the source of emf in maintaining the current in an electric circuit for a given time is called electric energy consumed in the circuit.', '\x08 Electric energy, W = VIt = P.t \x08 Electric energy = electric power × time SI unit of electric energy is joule, wherre 1 joule = 1 volt × 1 ampere × 1 second = 1 watt × 1 second The commercial unit of electric energy is called a kilowatt- hour (kWh) or Board to Trade Unit (BOT) or UNIT of Electricity, in brief, where 1 kWh = 1 kilo watt × 1 hour = 1000 watt × 1 hour Thus 1 kilo watt hour is the total electric energy consumed when an electrical appliance of power 1 kilo-watt works for one hours.', '1 kWh = 1000 Wh = (1000 W) × (60 × 60 s) = 3.6 × 10 6 J.', 'Note that the number of units of electricity consumed = No.', 'of kWh = watt hour 1000 \x04 2 2 Electric energy VI t I Rt V t / R \x02 \x02 \x02 13.3 Electricity Consumption (1) The price of electricity consumed is calculated on the basis of electrical energy and not on the basis of electrical power.', '(2) The unit Joule for energy is very small hence a big practical unit is considered known as kilowatt hour (KWH) or board of trade unit (B.T.U.) or simple unit.', '(3) 1 KWH or 1 unit is the quantity of electrical energy which dissipates in one hour in an electrical circuit when the electrical power in the circuit is 1 KWH thus 1 KWH = 1000 W \x04 3600 sec = 3.6 \x04 106 J.', 'JEE | NEET | Class 8 - 10 Download eSaral App www.esaral.com Rev.', 'Notes Class 12 Physics Chapter-2'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
