 the same quantity of water same quantity of water ts = t1 + t2 1 2 p 1 2 t t t t t \x01 \x02 (3) If three identical bulbs are connected in series as shown in figure then on closing the switch S.', 'Bulb C short circuited and hence illumination of bulbs A and B increases Reason : Voltage on A and B increased.', '(4) If three bulbs A, B and C are connected in mixed combination as shown, then illumination of bulb A decreases if either B or C gets fused Reason : Voltage on A decreases.', '(5) If two identical bulb A and B are connected in parallel with ammeter A and key K as shown in figure.', 'JEE | NEET | Class 8 - 10 Download eSaral App www.esaral.com Rev.', 'Notes Class 12 Physics Chapter-2'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
